We include capitalized costs associated with developing or obtaining internal-use software within long-term other assets, and these costs are amortized over the term of the relevant subscription period including any renewal options that are reasonably certain of being exercised. These costs include direct external costs of materials and services used in developing or obtaining the software and internal costs for employees directly associated with the software development project. As of December 31, 2022 and 2021, total costs capitalized for our internal-use software were $ 45 million and $ 48 million, respectively, net of accumulated amortization of $ 27 million and $ 11 million, respectively. During each of the years ended December 31, 2022, 2021 and 2020, we amortized $ 16 million, $ 10 million and $ 1 million, respectively, to selling, general and administrative expense.

